name: Woolsey CDR
text: Between their P-zones and Supreme or Meat Lovers pan crust pizzas, I could eat Pizza Hut multiple times a week. Especially when freshly cooked and still hot, I enjoy both the crust and the range of meats and vegetables. At the same time, I …More

name: Johnson Nguyen
text: Pizza came today with a guy that didn’t even greet me. Felt rude and nosey trying to stare past me and look at the inside of my house. Pizza came with inedible wing sauce splattered on it by accident I’m guessing which is gross.

name: Trisha Smith
text: Love this location.  Perfect pizza everytime!  Employee are always so polite and kind.

name: Avery Allen
text: Terrible customer service, disgusting pizza and overpriced menu items. My least favorite pizza place!

name: Jonathan Gibbs
text: If it's a busy night you're gonna wait a tad longer. It's worth it. I wish they'd bring gluten free crust more mainstream, but best #cheatnight #bangforyourbuck. This masterpiece was worth every penny.

name: Jennifer grimsley
text: Only brought one out of two pizza.  Had to wait for the second one and the guy didn't even said a word to me.  Just handed me the pizza and walked away.  Wow.  No worries.  We'll just eat one pizza and wait for over 20 minutes for our second one.

name: M
text: Ordered 6 pizzas for a work event, all turned out delicious. The main reason I’m reviewing is because of how pleasant the employees are. Their kindness and hospitality made me leave their store with a smile and a laugh. I appreciate their helpfulness too! Would definitely order from there again!

name: Sandra Galaska
text: Wow!  This store has some really bad reviews.  I was looking for reasonably priced, good pizza for a kids summer camp, and this is where I found it!  The store is now under new management. Candy Crosby, the manager, is fantastic!  I ordered …More

name: Bobby Lawson II
text: How hard is it to make a pizza the way you order it? They have been going down hill for a long time and guess I'm just a glutton for bad pizza.... Go anywhere else... So sad because they can make a really good pizza but no one they cares... At all....

name: Dominique LaMar
text:
Poor service, bad food
The store was located 0.7 miles from the hotel room. They forgot the marinara for the breadsticks and said all they could do was refund me for the marinara …More

text: Fresh, hot and right on time!  Manager was super nice.  Hard to find delivery drivers in Brentwood when unemployment is below 4% in one of the highest per capita zip codes in the USA.

text: Worst experience of my life. I waited 2 hours for a pizza to have it not show up at all. Will not be ordering EVER again.

name: Jhon Claus
text: Taz is the man. he went out his way to help me out tonight.

name: Seester A
text: This location needs to fix some kinks. Two hour waits and cold pizza. It will be awhile before I risk waiting two hours to spend over 15 bucks on cold food. You might have better luck if you can do carry out.

name: Nick Giaconia
text: They give the entire Pizza Hut organization a bad name.  Lazy and rude management, I can't possibly say enough bad things about them.  Go to Papa John's instead.

text: Great service and the pizzas were excellent! The staff was very helpful.

text: I called in to pick up the pizza and was told it would be ready in 20 minutes. When I got there they had not even started it. It was another 25 minutes before I got the pizza. Not good.

name: Justin Tinker
text: Rather than venting about all of their employee issues...they should just stick to pizza.  The lady literally ran her mouth the entire time. Beyond frustrating when all you are needing is your family’s dinner.
